<TITLE> No politics over Bangabandhu: Ershad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, Feb14 (bdnews24.com)Jatiya party chairman HM Ershad on Saturday said there should be no politics done over Bangabandhu's name. "Bangladesh was born because of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. He introduced Bangladesh to the world. That is why the world knows that Bangabandhu means Bangladesh. We should not do politics over his name" Ershad told a reception for leading citizens in Rangpur on Saturday. "It is our responsibility to recognise and evaluate contributions of all individuals to the cause of the society," said the former president. Ershad was speaking at a programme of Rangpur municipality that bestowed honours on eighteen accomplished citizens for their contributions to society. Chaired by municipality mayor Abdur Rauf Manik, the function at the Rangpur Central Shaheed Minar, was also addressed by Rowshan Ershad. The JP chairman said, "The people of this area have made significant contributions to the great language movement. I feel proud of paying honours to the citizens of Rangpur who have made contributions in education, literature, culture, sports, social service and music." Ershad added, "I am the son of Rangpur and prime minister Sheikh Hasina whom I call my sister is a daughter-in-law of Rangpur. We, brother and sister, will work together for the development of the Rangpur". bdnews
